[0.000, "o", "\u001b[96m\u001b[1m| \u001b[0m\u001b[90m Read     \u001b[0m.autoresearch/workflows/issue-9/iteration-6-opencode-review.log\r\nI will read the `iteration-6-opencode-review.log` file to see the results of the previous review.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[96m\u001b[1m| \u001b[0m\u001b[90m Read     \u001b[0mtests/test_extract_score.sh\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "I will read the `tests/test_extract_score.sh` file to understand how tests are currently implemented in this project.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "I will write the test script to `tests/test_archive.sh`.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[92m\u001b[1m| \u001b[0m\u001b[90m Write    \u001b[0mtests/test_archive.sh\r\nI have added `tests/test_archive.sh` with essential comments. The comments within the `archive_old_workflows` function are preserved from the original implementation in `run.sh` for consistency, and the headers are necessary for document structure and usage instructions.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\nNow, I will run the newly created tests.\r\n\u001b[91m\u001b[1m| \u001b[0m\u001b[90m Bash     \u001b[0mRun archive tests\r\n\r\n=== archive_old_workflows() Tests ===\r\n\r\nScenario 1: Archive multiple old issues\r\n[LOG] 已归档: issue-1 -> /var/folders/qj/vk5g8vfs09s94dg375c1db700000l2/T/tmp.RuNWF3p0zB/.autoresearch/archive/2026-04-19-issue-1\r\n[LOG] 已归档: issue-2 -> /var/folders/qj/vk5g8vfs09s94dg375c1db700000l2/T/tmp.RuNWF3p0zB/.autoresearch/archive/2026-04-19-issue-2\r\n"]
